CROSS-EXAMINATION TRANSCRIPT EXCERPT
Witness: Shri Anil Kumar Meena (Contractor's Resident Engineer)
Cross By: NHAI Counsel

Q: Did the Contractor submit written notice for delay within 28 days as per FIDIC 20.2?
A: Yes, multiple emails were sent by the Project Manager to the Independent Engineer.

Q: Were they properly stamped and acknowledged at the PIU office?
A: No written acknowledgement was given by PIU, they refused to sign the register.
(Adverse inference possible if email format contractually disputed)

Q: Why did the progress fall to 38% if your delays ended after 4 months?
A: Because NHAI withheld our running bills No. 4, 5, and 6, suffocating our cash flow. We suspended work under Clause 16.
